<!-- §9 What is a plush toy -->
<h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">What is a Plush Toy?</h2>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">A plush toy is a soft, stuffed fabric animal or character filled with synthetic material (usually polyester, cotton, or foam). Unlike traditional hard dolls or action figures, plushes are designed for cuddling, comfort, and emotional connection. They're tactile, huggable, and comforting.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Fluffy Rabbit Plush Toy specifically uses premium plush fabric and PP (polypropylene) cotton filling—denser and more durable than budget alternatives. The result is a plush that feels high-quality, holds its shape, and remains soft after repeated cuddling.</p>
<p style="color: var(--foreground); line-height: 1.6;">Plush toys serve multiple purposes: comfort objects, decorative pieces, gifts, and companions. They're especially popular in the cozy aesthetic space—think cottagecore, minimalist home décor, and gift-giving culture.</p>

